The paper deals with the study of quantum models of computation and their relationships with classical models. Therefore, cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses the implementation of quantum algorithms on different architectures, which suggests the possibility of cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) as a likely category. The paper also involves the analysis of algorithms, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper deals with quantum information theory, which could be categorized under cs.QI (Quantum Physics).
